1775956172172015	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEznAI		item.create	bn-2wnt	{"description":" maw v0.58.4 status: ws resolve --keep both now works! Resolved both bn-1u8wj and bn-j6gif without any Python scripting.   Minor quirk: bn-j6gif's first resolve call only handled one block out of two and reported \"1 file(s) still have   conflict markers\" — a second --keep both cleaned the rest. Looks like the resolver handles blocks one at a time but the   \"ready for merge\" state gate works correctly.","kind":"task","title":"note from agent using maw"}	blake3:hcfmkpUEz5xciCk8XU_SBOOhefxerQDlrgncIlq3EDc
1775960762765753	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErTQ		item.comment	bn-2wnt	{"body":"Investigated in v0.58.6. Findings:\n\n1. **`resolve_chunks` with `Some(\"both\")` on multi-block files works correctly in one pass** — verified by new regression test `resolve_both_handles_multiple_blocks_in_one_pass`. If the parser sees N blocks, all N get resolved.\n\n2. **The confusing \"1 file(s) still have conflict markers\" output IS a real bug** when per-block `--keep cf-N=...` is used: `run()` incremented `resolved_count` for any file where `resolve_chunks` returned Ok, even when some blocks were re-emitted as markers. That produced output like \"2 files resolved. 1 file still has conflict markers.\" with no indication which file was partial.\n\n3. **Fix**: `run()` now scans the resolved string for remaining `<<<<<<<` lines after writing. Fully-resolved files count toward `resolved_count`; partially-resolved files go into a new `partially_resolved` list that's reported separately with per-file block counts (\"resolved 1 block(s), 1 still marked\").\n\n4. **The original agent scenario (`--keep both` partial resolution) could not be reproduced**. Possible explanations: (a) the file had a parser-confusing structure like an unbalanced nested marker that collapsed two logical blocks into one; (b) the user's perception of \"2 blocks\" may have been \"2 files\" or similar. Added a regression test for the 2-block `--keep both` happy path anyway.\n\nClosing as the reporting quirk is fixed. If the real parser issue reappears with a reproducible input, reopen with the file content."}	blake3:3AnqLMwgP4sdPLG5zaafy1QNpoimrqC4uPIxsA6771I
