1776553920406066	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyygo		item.create	bn-3o8k	{"description":"The `--status-bar` fast path (count_dirty_tracked in crates/maw-git/src/status_impl.rs) only compares mtime+size against the index stat cache. It never content-hashes stat-mismatched files, so any mtime change vs. the index — checkout, touch, filesystem remounts — produces spurious dirty counts.\n\nRepro (verified in ~/src/ward):\n  cd ~/src/ward/ws/default && find . -maxdepth 3 -name '*.md' | head -5 | xargs -I {} touch -d '2020-01-01' {}\n  maw status --status-bar   # shows 5 extra changed files\n  maw exec default -- git status  # refreshes index stats\n  maw status --status-bar   # back to correct count\n\nReal `git status` content-hashes mismatched entries: if the blob hash matches the index OID, the file is clean and git refreshes the stat cache. That is why running git status 'fixes' the count.\n\nFix: in count_dirty_tracked, when stat differs, hash the file and compare to the index entry OID before counting it dirty. Fast case (stat matches) stays fast; slow case only hits files that actually differ by stat.\n\nFiles:\n  crates/maw-git/src/status_impl.rs:83  (count_dirty_tracked)\n  crates/maw-cli/src/status.rs:742       (caller)","kind":"task","title":"maw status --status-bar reports false dirty files after mtime skew"}	blake3:MePwcfho_lPPOkpbV0SaoeJfdTJDWPusQp2auFrSX0k
