1776611409862740	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyzgo		item.create	bn-2538	{"description":"The test 'stale_workspace_overlapping_change_produces_conflict' in src/merge/build_phase.rs asserts that a stale workspace overlapping an epoch-delta produces a conflict. It has been failing since commit d548cd7 introduced the 'ws_has_commits' path in src/merge/collect.rs.\n\nRoot cause: the test helpers (make_workspace_with_modified_file etc.) create ws_path as a plain subdirectory of the outer test git repo. Inside ws_path, 'git rev-parse HEAD' walks up and returns the OUTER repo's HEAD (= current_epoch), which collect_one interprets as 'the workspace has committed changes' (since current_epoch != initial_epoch). It then reads file content via 'git cat-file blob HEAD:<path>' — again walking up to the outer repo — so the stale workspace's reported content is the current_epoch version, not the actual bytes written to ws_path on disk.\n\nResult: both stale-workspace patchsets report the same content, all_equal() short-circuits, no conflict emitted. The sibling tests (non_overlapping, diff3_auto_resolve) were passing coincidentally — they either touched a file absent from the outer HEAD or happened to produce the same merged content.\n\nFix: run 'git init' inside each test ws_path to stop upward discovery. HEAD is unborn, so ws_has_commits returns false and collect correctly reads the workspace file from disk. No production code changes.\n\nNot a regression in production — in a bare-repo setup every ws_path is a real worktree with its own .git marker, so discovery stays local.","kind":"task","title":"fix(test): stale_workspace_overlapping_change_produces_conflict false-pass setup"}	blake3:YB39qjleOXLm2pGJ6XO07MzanvGpcIRTWf-n1YBWkLg
