1776632598240371	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEy1go		item.create	bn-gb8f	{"description":"tests/recovery_capture.rs:156 — after destroy-recreate-destroy cycle, `maw ws history repeat-cycle --format json` returns operations[] with zero destroy entries, so the assertion 'at least two destroy history entries' fails.\n\nCommand: cargo test --release --test recovery_capture repeated_destroy_cycles_preserve_capture_history\n\nPre-existing on main (verified by stashing unrelated bn-31v8 fix and running — still fails with 'got: 0'). Unrelated to the DST issue.\n\nEither the workspace history feature lost ability to surface destroy events for the same workspace name across cycles, or the test expectation no longer matches the current oplog schema. Needs investigation of ws history / oplog semantics for recreated workspaces with same name.","kind":"task","title":"test: repeated_destroy_cycles_preserve_capture_history failing"}	blake3:8LWS6xir1yfUabA6I9zVHVORNlTUkhU4Gu3ef1wxjXk
