1776728683117738	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuws		item.create	bn-nsz0	{"description":"**Parent goal**: bn-2xgi (gjm8 initiative). Must close before gjm8 is considered done — the goal's exit criteria include \"Executable bit, symlinks round-trip through replay.\"\n\n**Issue**: `Added` files lose their mode during rebase. `apply::infer_mode_for_new_file` hard-codes `EntryMode::Blob` rather than consulting the patch's `FileChange.mode`. `Modified` paths correctly preserve exec/symlink modes (covered by unit tests in `apply.rs`), but a file that is newly introduced inside a workspace commit and then rebased loses 100755 / 120000 and becomes 100644.\n\n**Evidence**: Two `#[ignore]`'d tests in `tests/sync_rebase_semantics.rs` (added in bn-28rd):\n- `sync_rebase_preserves_executable_bit` — a workspace commit adding a new exec file; after rebase the tree entry is 100644.\n- `sync_rebase_preserves_symlink` — same pattern for symlinks.\n\nBoth test bodies are written and currently ignored. Un-ignoring them is the acceptance criterion.\n\n**Root cause**: Phase 3 added `FileChange.mode: Option<EntryMode>` and Phase 3's `diff_patchset` populates it from `DiffEntry.new_mode`. Phase 2's `apply_unilateral_patchset` for added-path cases calls `infer_mode_for_new_file` which always returns `EntryMode::Blob` — ignoring the available `FileChange.mode` field.\n\n**Fix**: In `maw-core::merge::apply`, thread `FileChange.mode` into `MaterializedEntry.mode` for the Added path. Probably one to three lines of code. Remove the TODO at the `infer_mode_for_new_file` site.\n\n**Tests**: Un-ignore the two tests in `tests/sync_rebase_semantics.rs`. Add a unit test in `apply.rs` asserting Added exec/symlink preservation if not already covered.\n\n**Size**: xs.","kind":"bug","labels":["gjm8","mode-preservation"],"parent":"bn-2xgi","size":"xs","title":"Thread FileChange.mode through apply for Added paths (exec bit + symlinks)","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:D6GAUSQtLkPtePDIBYxbaEcWJai-LouztSaPjBSzuHM
