1777232777787790	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEypww		item.create	bn-2jpn	{"description":"## Scope (sub-bone of bn-5kad, hot-path subset)\n\nReplace the 6 production git CLI subprocess calls in `src/merge/collect.rs` with maw-git / gix equivalents. These are in the merge collect phase — the hot path that already produced the non-ASCII filename bug — and all six are simple read-only / blob-write operations with available gix replacements.\n\n## Calls to replace\n\n| Line | Call | Replacement |\n|---|---|---|\n| 305 | `git rev-parse refs/manifold/epoch/current` (in repo_root) | `gix` ref lookup |\n| 321 | `git merge-base HEAD <oid>` (in ws_path) | `gix` merge-base / commit graph |\n| 342 | `git cat-file -e <commit>:<path>` | `gix` tree entry lookup |\n| 384 | `git rev-parse HEAD` | `gix` HEAD resolve |\n| 406 | `git cat-file blob HEAD:<path>` | `gix` blob read via tree |\n| 449 | `git hash-object -w --stdin` | `gix` write blob |\n\nPath 342 / 406 are the unicode-vulnerable ones — `HEAD:<path>` formatting via `PathBuf::display()` is what burned us before.\n\n## Out of scope (deliberately)\n- Test-helper Command::new(\"git\") calls inside this file (test setup, fine to leave)\n- working_copy.rs — separate follow-up; many of its calls are gix-blocked (detached HEAD worktree ops, stash apply)\n- The other ~28 files in bn-5kad\n\n## Done when\n- Zero `Command::new(\"git\")` calls in production code paths of `src/merge/collect.rs`\n- Existing merge tests pass (including any unicode-filename test)\n- No new gix CLI dependencies introduced\n\nParent: bn-5kad","kind":"task","title":"Replace 6 git CLI calls in merge/collect.rs with gix"}	blake3:ez1-y_6kbO7HQ2EvFhC1kxTQ1CQjmxWXuh792eDZK80
